 thresholds approach each\nother, and then the Seebeck coefficient and the figure of merit increase\nsignificantly, as expected from the general arguments of Mahan and Sofo [J. D.\nMahan and J. O. Sofo, Proc. Natl. Acad. Sci. U.S.A. 93, 7436 (1996)] for a\nnarrow energy-range of the zero-temperature metallic behavior.\n","versions":[{"version":"v1","created":"Wed, 26 Jul 2017 04:57:01 GMT"},{"version":"v2","created":"Fri, 6 Oct 2017 02:21:31 GMT"}],"update_date":"2017-10-09"}
